1. *Novosti* iz politike su danas dominirale u medijima. (News from politics dominated the media today.)
2. Na naslovnoj strani novina su se pojavile *novosti* o incidentu u gradu. (The front page of the newspaper featured news about an incident in the city.)
3. Uvek me zanima koje *novosti* imaju moji prijatelji iz inostranstva. (I'm always interested in what news my friends from abroad have.)
4. Nisam bio siguran da li su *novosti* koje sam čuo istinite. (I wasn't sure if the news I heard was true.)
5. Zašto ne proveriš *novosti* na internetu umesto da gledaš televiziju? (Why don't you check the news on the internet instead of watching TV?)
6. Neću moći da se vidim s tobom danas, moram pratiti *novosti* u vezi s poslom. (I won't be able to meet you today, I need to follow the news about work.)
7. Ovaj sajt ima mnogo korisnih *novosti* o zdravom životu. (This website has a lot of useful news about a healthy lifestyle.)
8. *Novosti* koje je podijelio kolega nisu me iznenadile. (The news shared by my colleague did not surprise me.)
9. Ukoliko želite biti informisani o najnovijim *novostima*, pretplatite se na našu novinsku listu. (If you want to be informed about the latest news, subscribe to our newsletter.)
10. Kada su *novosti* o novom zakonu objavljene, svi su bili zbunjeni. (When news about the new law was released, everyone was confused.)